[src:golang/encoding-json] Unmarshal parses the JSON-encoded data and stores the result in the value pointed to by v.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If v is nil or not a pointer, Unmarshal returns an InvalidUnmarshalError.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal JSON into a pointer, Unmarshal first handles the case of the JSON being the JSON literal null.
[src:golang/encoding-json] In that case, Unmarshal sets the pointer to nil.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Otherwise, Unmarshal unmarshals the JSON into the value pointed at by the pointer.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If the pointer is nil, Unmarshal allocates a new value for it to point to.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal JSON into a value implementing Unmarshaler, Unmarshal calls that value's Unmarshaler.UnmarshalJSON method, including when the input is a JSON null.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Otherwise, if the value implements encoding.TextUnmarshaler and the input is a JSON quoted string, Unmarshal calls encoding.TextUnmarshaler.UnmarshalText with the unquoted form of the string.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal JSON into a struct, Unmarshal matches incoming object keys to the keys used by Marshal (either the struct field name or its tag), ignoring case.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If multiple struct fields match an object key, an exact case match is preferred over a case-insensitive one.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Incoming object members are processed in the order observed.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If an object includes duplicate keys, later duplicates will replace or be merged into prior values.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal a JSON array into a slice, Unmarshal resets the slice length to zero and then appends each element to the slice.
[src:golang/encoding-json] As a special case, to unmarshal an empty JSON array into a slice, Unmarshal replaces the slice with a new empty slice.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal a JSON array into a Go array, Unmarshal decodes JSON array elements into corresponding Go array elements.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If the Go array is smaller than the JSON array, the additional JSON array elements are discarded.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If the JSON array is smaller than the Go array, the additional Go array elements are set to zero values.
[src:golang/encoding-json] To unmarshal a JSON object into a map, Unmarshal first establishes a map to use.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If the map is nil, Unmarshal allocates a new map.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Otherwise Unmarshal reuses the existing map, keeping existing entries.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Unmarshal then stores key-value pairs from the JSON object into the map.
[src:golang/encoding-json] The map's key type must either be any string type, an integer, or implement encoding.TextUnmarshaler.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If the JSON-encoded data contain a syntax error, Unmarshal returns a SyntaxError.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If a JSON value is not appropriate for a given target type, or if a JSON number overflows the target type, Unmarshal skips that field and completes the unmarshaling as best it can.
[src:golang/encoding-json] If no more serious errors are encountered, Unmarshal returns an UnmarshalTypeError describing the earliest such error.
[src:golang/encoding-json] In any case, it's not guaranteed that all the remaining fields following the problematic one will be unmarshaled into the target object.
[src:golang/encoding-json] The JSON null value unmarshals into an interface, map, pointer, or slice by setting that Go value to nil.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Because null is often used in JSON to mean “not present,” unmarshaling a JSON null into any other Go type has no effect on the value and produces no error.
[src:golang/encoding-json] When unmarshaling quoted strings, invalid UTF-8 or invalid UTF-16 surrogate pairs are not treated as an error.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Instead, they are replaced by the Unicode replacement character U+FFFD.
[src:golang/encoding-json] Valid reports whether data is a valid JSON encoding.
[src:golang/encoding-json] A Decoder reads and decodes JSON values from an input stream.
